  "prompt": "How much does it cost to set up a new mobile company in India? In a small scale?",
  "response": "Setting up a small-scale mobile company in India can vary in cost, but here's a rough breakdown:\n\nInitial Investment Range:\n- Minimum: \u20b95-10 lakhs (approximately $6,000-$12,000)\n- Moderate Scale: \u20b915-25 lakhs ($18,000-$30,000)\n\nKey Cost Components:\n1. Business Registration\n- Private Limited Company: \u20b96,000-\u20b910,000\n- GST Registration: \u20b9500-\u20b91,000\n\n2. Infrastructure\n- Small Office/Workspace: \u20b950,000-\u20b92,00,000\n- Basic Computer/IT Equipment: \u20b91-3 lakhs\n- Initial Inventory: \u20b92-5 lakhs\n\n3. Licenses and Permits\n- Trade License: \u20b95,000-\u20b910,000\n- Mobile Selling License: \u20b910,000-\u20b925,000\n\n4. Marketing and Initial Operational Expenses\n- Initial Marketing: \u20b950,000-\u20b91,50,000\n- Staff Salary: \u20b91-2 lakhs per month\n\n5. Working Capital\n- Recommended: \u20b93-5 lakhs\n\nAdditional factors influencing cost:\n- Location\n- Business model\n- Inventory strategy\n- Marketing approach\n\nThese are approximate figures and can vary based on specific circumstances.",
